WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.675 --> 00:00:09.677
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:58.036 --> 00:02:02.206
[squire] Aeron Bracken. the worst horseman
among us and yet the first to be knighted.

3
00:02:02.290 --> 00:02:03.290
[squires laughing]

4
00:02:03.333 --> 00:02:05.418
[Aeron] Must be my swordsmanship.

5
00:02:05.501 --> 00:02:06.417
[all laughing]

6
00:02:06.419 --> 00:02:07.837
Can you even get that thing up?

7
00:02:08.421 --> 00:02:10.590
- Well enough for killing Blackwoods.
- [squires laugh]

8
00:02:10.673 --> 00:02:11.799
[man] Bracken!

9
00:02:14.302 --> 00:02:16.012
[horse neighs]

10
00:02:16.095 --> 00:02:17.263
[sheep bleats]

11
00:02:17.889 --> 00:02:20.683
Put the boundary stones back.

12
00:02:21.851 --> 00:02:23.311
We didn't move them.

13
00:02:23.394 --> 00:02:25.313
Did they move themselves. then?

14
00:02:25.396 --> 00:02:28.983
Just rolled their way over so Bracken cows
can fill their bellies on Blackwood grass?

15
00:02:29.067 --> 00:02:31.486
- The assize at Riverrun...
- Fuck the assize.

16
00:02:32.612 --> 00:02:35.948
And fuck you. This is our land.

17
00:02:42.372 --> 00:02:43.664
It's Bracken land.

18
00:02:48.169 --> 00:02:50.046
- Babe killer.
- [man] What did you say?

19
00:02:55.635 --> 00:02:58.721
Your false queen. Rhaenyra is a kinslayer.

20
00:03:00.223 --> 00:03:03.267
Your uncle declared for Aegon. did he?

21
00:03:06.562 --> 00:03:09.649
Well. then. let me tell you.

22
00:03:10.483 --> 00:03:14.779
Aegon Targaryen is no true king.

23
00:03:15.863 --> 00:03:19.409
Just as you are no true knight.

24
00:03:20.493 --> 00:03:24.497
You're both craven. little cunts!

25
00:03:28.960 --> 00:03:31.212
[laughing]

26
00:03:34.465 --> 00:03:35.925
You wouldn't dare.

27
00:03:37.301 --> 00:03:39.220
- [swords clanging]
- [men shouting]

28
00:03:39.303 --> 00:03:41.305
[ominous music playing]

29
00:03:42.181 --> 00:03:43.724
[flies buzzing]

30
00:04:18.593 --> 00:04:20.470
[Jace] He is the basest of villains.

31
00:04:21.471 --> 00:04:23.222
He sullies the grave of his brother.

32
00:04:25.600 --> 00:04:28.060
I cannot fault him for keeping his oath.

33
00:04:31.230 --> 00:04:33.232
And what of those who sent him?

34
00:04:55.254 --> 00:04:57.673
Otto Hightower would never
have allowed this.

35
00:05:00.426 --> 00:05:02.595
Hotter blood has prevailed. I think.

36
00:05:04.096 --> 00:05:05.976
The young men have taken
the bit in their teeth.

37
00:05:06.057 --> 00:05:07.725
They wish to punish. to avenge.

38
00:05:10.228 --> 00:05:12.230
Soon they will not even
remember what it was

39
00:05:12.313 --> 00:05:14.440
that began the war in the first place.

40
00:05:14.524 --> 00:05:16.817
That is easy enough.
They usurped my throne.

41
00:05:16.901 --> 00:05:18.402
That is one answer.

42
00:05:22.823 --> 00:05:25.117
Or was it when the child was beheaded?

43
00:05:27.703 --> 00:05:29.789
Or when Aemond killed Luke?

44
00:05:33.543 --> 00:05:35.670
Or when Luke took Aemond's eye?

45
00:05:37.630 --> 00:05:39.966
We teeter now at the point
where none of it will matter.

46
00:05:41.801 --> 00:05:45.930
When the desire to kill and burn
takes hold and reason is forgotten.

47
00:05:48.349 --> 00:05:50.059
There may be another way.

48
00:05:54.063 --> 00:05:55.523
Alicent Hightower.

49
00:05:56.065 --> 00:05:58.109
[poignant music playing]

50
00:06:00.236 --> 00:06:03.573
When last we met.
Alicent said I would make a fine queen.

51
00:06:04.490 --> 00:06:06.284
You've seen what has happened since then.

52
00:06:06.367 --> 00:06:08.512
She came to me in the hours
after your lord father's death.

53
00:06:08.536 --> 00:06:09.704
She knows war is coming.

54
00:06:09.787 --> 00:06:12.331
And that it'll be savage
beyond all compare.

55
00:06:13.916 --> 00:06:18.713
There is no war so hateful to the gods
as a war between kin.

56
00:06:22.842 --> 00:06:25.720
And no war so bloody
as a war between dragons.

57
00:06:26.971 --> 00:06:28.848
I do not believe she wants it.

58
00:06:28.931 --> 00:06:30.308
She sent a raven.

59
00:06:32.143 --> 00:06:35.187
I do not care to read her message.
What she did...

60
00:06:35.271 --> 00:06:37.690
It is not her but the men around her
who seek bloodshed.

61
00:06:37.773 --> 00:06:38.899
She permitted it.

62
00:06:41.110 --> 00:06:44.113
As you permitted the murder
of a little boy in his bed?

63
00:06:52.580 --> 00:06:56.751
Alicent is in King's Landing.
Her son sits my throne.

64
00:06:59.295 --> 00:07:01.255
There is nothing more to be said.

65
00:07:16.228 --> 00:07:17.647
[squire] You're well. Lord Hand?

66
00:07:19.899 --> 00:07:21.025
[sighs]

67
00:07:21.817 --> 00:07:23.819
Only. they'll be waiting.

68
00:07:24.945 --> 00:07:26.322
[bell tolling]

69
00:07:26.656 --> 00:07:28.783
[indistinct chatter]

70
00:07:33.496 --> 00:07:35.915
[knights chatting indistinctly]

71
00:07:35.998 --> 00:07:37.917
[suspenseful music playing]

72
00:07:39.168 --> 00:07:40.169
[Ned] My lord.

73
00:07:40.252 --> 00:07:42.588
[Martyn] Hm? Oh. [clears throat]

74
00:07:43.255 --> 00:07:44.840
[bell continues tolling]

75
00:08:04.402 --> 00:08:06.445
...though I understand
there have been tidings in...

76
00:08:15.496 --> 00:08:17.873
[Cole] Good morrow. Your Grace. My lords.

77
00:08:23.295 --> 00:08:24.295
[Alicent clears throat]

78
00:08:26.590 --> 00:08:28.134
Forgive my lateness.

79
00:08:28.217 --> 00:08:30.136
Important business. no doubt.

80
00:08:30.219 --> 00:08:33.222
You've appointed new knights
to the Kingsguard. Your Grace.

81
00:08:33.305 --> 00:08:36.559
- To replace those we lost.
- The last one needlessly. some might say.

82
00:08:39.645 --> 00:08:42.732
Ser Arryk was awarded the great duty
of ending Rhaenyra's challenge.

83
00:08:42.815 --> 00:08:44.233
He failed to discharge it.

84
00:08:44.316 --> 00:08:46.712
- He failed because the scheme was rash.
- Perhaps. Your Grace.

85
00:08:46.736 --> 00:08:49.447
but we cannot all hide in our castles
waiting for war to come to us.

86
00:08:49.530 --> 00:08:51.115
As now it surely will.

87
00:08:51.198 --> 00:08:53.367
[Aemond] As now it already has.

88
00:08:54.326 --> 00:08:57.455
House Bracken took it upon themselves
to attack the Blackwoods.

89
00:08:57.538 --> 00:08:59.582
who declared for the pretender.

90
00:08:59.665 --> 00:09:01.792
Lord Samwell Blackwood himself is slain.

91
00:09:01.876 --> 00:09:04.003
Good. First blood in our name.

92
00:09:05.087 --> 00:09:07.465
Both sides took heavy losses. Your Grace.

93
00:09:08.048 --> 00:09:11.343
I'm not entirely certain
we can declare this a victory.

94
00:09:11.427 --> 00:09:13.721
The Blackwoods and Brackens
have feuded for centuries.

95
00:09:13.804 --> 00:09:15.723
This is nothing more
than an excuse for them

96
00:09:15.806 --> 00:09:18.184
to indulge their ancient grudge.
It's no true war.

97
00:09:19.935 --> 00:09:21.729
[Aegon] Call it what you will.

98
00:09:21.812 --> 00:09:23.439
I call it war.

99
00:09:24.774 --> 00:09:25.941
And so will Dragonstone.

100
00:09:26.859 --> 00:09:30.780
The question is.
what are we going to do about it?

101
00:09:36.327 --> 00:09:38.579
We send a raven to Lord Tully.

102
00:09:39.330 --> 00:09:41.582
These houses are his vassals.
are they not?

103
00:09:41.665 --> 00:09:42.875
He must control them.

104
00:09:42.958 --> 00:09:47.671
Lord Grover Tully is a flaccid. old fool
who couldn't control his cock in a cunny.

105
00:09:48.172 --> 00:09:49.590
Begging your pardon. Your Grace.

106
00:09:49.673 --> 00:09:51.777
[Aegon] Do you have
any better suggestions. Lord Jasper?

107
00:09:51.801 --> 00:09:55.846
Your uncle Ormund marches from Oldtown
at the head of a great host. Your Grace.

108
00:09:55.930 --> 00:09:58.182
And your brother Daeron's dragon
nears fighting age.

109
00:09:58.265 --> 00:10:01.453
- Call on them to suppress the Riverlands.
- [Tyland] Alas. they are months away.

110
00:10:01.477 --> 00:10:04.772
My lord brother Jason is raising
a great army at Casterly Rock.

111
00:10:04.855 --> 00:10:08.442
In a matter of weeks. he will be able
to harass the Blackwoods from the west.

112
00:10:08.526 --> 00:10:11.570
Should we not aim to unite these armies
and then strike as one?

113
00:10:11.654 --> 00:10:14.657
[laughs] Ah. the great
military mind of the Citadel.

114
00:10:14.740 --> 00:10:18.160
Do remind me. which link in your chain
denotes the art of war?

115
00:10:18.244 --> 00:10:20.472
This council must rediscover
the discipline it lately had

116
00:10:20.496 --> 00:10:21.956
if it's to be of any use.

117
00:10:22.039 --> 00:10:23.666
The Riverlands are the key to the war.

118
00:10:24.792 --> 00:10:26.669
Harrenhal is the key to the Riverlands.

119
00:10:27.503 --> 00:10:29.672
I will ride out
with those I can muster here.

120
00:10:29.755 --> 00:10:31.131
Men I know. men I've trained.

121
00:10:31.215 --> 00:10:34.093
You need time to raise the numbers
to challenge the Rivermen.

122
00:10:34.176 --> 00:10:35.511
Speed is my ally.

123
00:10:35.594 --> 00:10:38.681
I will turn the Crownland houses
who declared for Rhaenyra to our cause.

124
00:10:38.764 --> 00:10:41.433
We will add their numbers to our own
and then turn west.

125
00:10:41.517 --> 00:10:45.187
where I will enlist the Brackens.
subdue the Riverlands.

126
00:10:45.729 --> 00:10:46.856
and take Harrenhal.

127
00:10:48.107 --> 00:10:50.317
[Alicent] So impatient
to ride with so few men.

128
00:10:50.943 --> 00:10:53.654
So like to be destroyed
by the first stronghold you meet.

129
00:10:53.737 --> 00:10:56.240
- A bold scheme. indeed.
- The gods favor the bold.

130
00:10:56.323 --> 00:10:57.533
They did not favor Ser Arryk.

131
00:10:57.616 --> 00:10:58.701
[chuckles]

132
00:11:00.035 --> 00:11:01.745
What say you. my king?

133
00:11:03.789 --> 00:11:06.125
And you'll take Aemond and Vhagar?

134
00:11:06.208 --> 00:11:08.294
[Cole] Vhagar will remain here.

135
00:11:09.670 --> 00:11:10.838
To defend the city.

136
00:11:12.006 --> 00:11:14.216
Good. To war. then.

137
00:11:14.758 --> 00:11:15.885
Hm.

138
00:11:16.510 --> 00:11:17.678
I'll come too. with Sunfyre.

139
00:11:17.761 --> 00:11:18.947
- [Alicent] Aegon.
- [Cole] Your Grace.

140
00:11:18.971 --> 00:11:21.241
- [Aegon] You'll need a dragon.
- [Cole] My plan is not to draw attention.

141
00:11:21.265 --> 00:11:25.352
And what will you do if you encounter
one or more of Rhaenyra's dragons?

142
00:11:25.436 --> 00:11:26.876
She'll want to answer for Ser Arryk.

143
00:11:26.937 --> 00:11:29.690
We will be more like to encounter one
if we field one of our own.

144
00:11:29.773 --> 00:11:32.860
[Aemond] That is precisely
why you must remain. brother.

145
00:11:32.943 --> 00:11:36.238
It's a brave thought.
but we cannot risk your loss.

146
00:11:40.784 --> 00:11:42.661
I'm as fearsome as any of them.

147
00:11:48.042 --> 00:11:48.958
[sighs] Oh.

148
00:11:48.959 --> 00:11:50.753
[dragon screeching]

149
00:11:52.671 --> 00:11:54.924
[pensive music playing]

150
00:11:59.011 --> 00:12:01.013
[footsteps approaching]

151
00:12:09.438 --> 00:12:12.524
[Rhaenyra] I was told you turned back
from your ship to bring warning.

152
00:12:12.608 --> 00:12:15.319
I was not believed. at first.

153
00:12:15.402 --> 00:12:16.528
You saved my life.

154
00:12:17.404 --> 00:12:20.616
And what is the life of a queen worth
these days?

155
00:12:20.699 --> 00:12:22.534
Hm. You wish to be rewarded.

156
00:12:23.285 --> 00:12:25.746
As I would think
you would wish to reward me.

157
00:12:25.829 --> 00:12:27.706
[dragon screeches]

158
00:12:28.958 --> 00:12:33.045
- What price would you set?
- A place at your court.

159
00:12:37.091 --> 00:12:39.426
You said your earnest desire
was to flee Westeros.

160
00:12:39.510 --> 00:12:40.719
And you let me go.

161
00:12:41.387 --> 00:12:44.390
You showed me grace
when you could have withheld it.

162
00:12:46.308 --> 00:12:47.893
I'm not often surprised.

163
00:12:52.272 --> 00:12:53.691
One turn for another. then.

164
00:12:55.192 --> 00:12:57.361
I know the workings of the Red Keep

165
00:12:57.444 --> 00:12:59.947
and the movements
of those who serve there.

166
00:13:00.698 --> 00:13:02.908
That is worth more than gold to you now.

167
00:13:04.118 --> 00:13:05.661
And what is my worth to you?

168
00:13:06.787 --> 00:13:08.330
[dragon screeches]

169
00:13:09.790 --> 00:13:12.960
I would punish the Hightowers
for what they have done.

170
00:13:13.043 --> 00:13:16.422
To me. to those who served me.

171
00:13:17.339 --> 00:13:22.177
But more than that. I know the struggles
of the smallfolk of King's Landing.

172
00:13:22.261 --> 00:13:26.098
They will be ruled.
either by you or by the usurper.

173
00:13:27.057 --> 00:13:29.977
And only one of you
has shown yourself to be merciful.

174
00:13:31.145 --> 00:13:33.772
I hope you do not confuse mercy
with pliancy.

175
00:13:35.816 --> 00:13:36.900
[dragon screeches]

176
00:13:37.484 --> 00:13:39.278
Are they always like this?

177
00:13:40.446 --> 00:13:43.073
Seasmoke. my late lord husband's dragon.

178
00:13:44.199 --> 00:13:47.536
He's grown restless of late.
We cannot know why.

179
00:13:47.619 --> 00:13:49.329
Maybe he's lonely.

180
00:13:58.255 --> 00:13:59.256
[Rhaenyra] Rhaena.

181
00:14:01.133 --> 00:14:02.134
Your Grace.

182
00:14:05.012 --> 00:14:09.725
I've decided to send Joffrey to ward
with my cousin. the Lady Jeyne Arryn.

183
00:14:10.350 --> 00:14:12.686
She has pledged an army
in return for a dragon.

184
00:14:12.770 --> 00:14:13.771
So she will have one.

185
00:14:14.438 --> 00:14:16.065
Aegon and Viserys will accompany him.

186
00:14:16.148 --> 00:14:18.233
until a place of greater safety
can be found.

187
00:14:18.317 --> 00:14:19.943
Tyraxes is but a hatchling.

188
00:14:20.569 --> 00:14:22.780
- And Stormcloud...
- I want you to go with them.

189
00:14:25.199 --> 00:14:27.242
The Red Keep is in disarray.

190
00:14:27.326 --> 00:14:28.966
They have sent one assassin in the night.

191
00:14:28.994 --> 00:14:30.913
and their dragons are ever
a short flight away.

192
00:14:31.580 --> 00:14:34.124
You must take the little ones further.
To Pentos. I think.

193
00:14:34.666 --> 00:14:36.126
Where my mother died.

194
00:14:36.210 --> 00:14:38.504
It is safer than anywhere in Westeros.

195
00:14:39.546 --> 00:14:43.050
Write to Prince Reggio.
If he will have you. then go to him.

196
00:14:44.176 --> 00:14:45.552
I'm sorry to put this upon you.

197
00:14:46.220 --> 00:14:50.265
It breaks my heart to send my boys away.
not knowing when I will see them again.

198
00:14:50.349 --> 00:14:52.893
But you have seen
what may befall them here.

199
00:14:53.644 --> 00:14:54.645
Rhaena.

200
00:14:56.730 --> 00:14:59.024
I need you to be the mother to them
that I cannot.

201
00:15:01.026 --> 00:15:05.030
Teach them. train them.
guard them as a dragon guards her eggs.

202
00:15:05.114 --> 00:15:06.240
And my sister?

203
00:15:08.075 --> 00:15:10.035
- I need Baela here.
- Because she has a dragon.

204
00:15:10.119 --> 00:15:11.829
I cannot promise to make you happy.

205
00:15:12.412 --> 00:15:16.041
But I ask you.
make this sacrifice willingly.

206
00:15:16.625 --> 00:15:17.709
For all of us.

207
00:15:19.586 --> 00:15:20.587
Your Grace.

208
00:15:27.094 --> 00:15:28.929
[dramatic music playing]

209
00:15:29.012 --> 00:15:30.180
[thunder rumbling]

210
00:15:30.264 --> 00:15:31.849
[dragon screeches]

211
00:15:58.709 --> 00:15:59.710
[guard] Dragon!

212
00:16:00.836 --> 00:16:02.337
[indistinct shouting]

213
00:16:06.216 --> 00:16:08.218
[roaring]

214
00:16:12.014 --> 00:16:13.432
[low growling]

215
00:16:15.184 --> 00:16:17.060
[dragon screeches]

216
00:16:17.144 --> 00:16:19.563
[raindrops pattering]

217
00:16:19.646 --> 00:16:21.648
[footsteps approaching]

218
00:16:27.779 --> 00:16:29.865
[thunder rumbling]

219
00:16:41.251 --> 00:16:43.045
[creaking]

220
00:17:15.285 --> 00:17:17.746
[high-pitched squeaking and fluttering]

221
00:17:17.829 --> 00:17:19.831
[screeching]

222
00:17:21.250 --> 00:17:22.459
[voice] Daemon!

223
00:18:06.920 --> 00:18:08.630
[voice] Daemon!

224
00:18:24.187 --> 00:18:25.272
[distant clanking]

225
00:18:26.940 --> 00:18:28.233
[clanking]

226
00:18:34.239 --> 00:18:35.240
Halt!

227
00:18:37.034 --> 00:18:38.160
[grunts]

228
00:18:41.538 --> 00:18:43.206
- [man 1 gasps]
- [man 2] Run!

229
00:18:43.290 --> 00:18:44.916
[indistinct shouting]

230
00:18:49.421 --> 00:18:51.048
[Daemon] I'm claiming Harrenhal.

231
00:18:53.967 --> 00:18:55.260
Apparently so.

232
00:19:17.074 --> 00:19:20.243
I. Ser Simon Strong.
Castellan of Harrenhal.

233
00:19:20.327 --> 00:19:23.038
pledge fealty to Rhaenyra
of House Targaryen.

234
00:19:23.121 --> 00:19:24.456
First of Her Name.

235
00:19:25.207 --> 00:19:27.793
I swear this by the old gods and the new.

236
00:19:29.586 --> 00:19:32.339
Supper is venison
with black cabbage and peas.

237
00:19:33.548 --> 00:19:36.718
No red currant. Sorry about that.

238
00:19:45.560 --> 00:19:47.270
[Simon] That venison is well-aged.

239
00:19:48.855 --> 00:19:50.482
Shame to let it waste.

240
00:19:54.486 --> 00:19:55.904
I've survived many a battle.

241
00:19:55.987 --> 00:19:58.615
I do not mean to be felled
by poisoned peas.

242
00:19:58.698 --> 00:19:59.950
[Simon chuckles]

243
00:20:00.033 --> 00:20:04.454
I'll admit that my cook's peas aren't
exactly the stuff of legend. But poison?

244
00:20:04.955 --> 00:20:06.873
[Daemon] It's an easy way
to kill a dragonrider.

245
00:20:09.751 --> 00:20:12.379
If you've not yet surmised.
you are welcome here.

246
00:20:13.255 --> 00:20:15.966
And what of your lord. Larys Strong?

247
00:20:16.633 --> 00:20:17.633
Hm?

248
00:20:18.301 --> 00:20:23.181
- He who sits at the false court of Aegon?
- Larys Clubfoot is no lord of mine.

249
00:20:24.808 --> 00:20:27.853
He's a scourge upon this castle
and this family.

250
00:20:29.271 --> 00:20:31.940
Do you not think it strange
that his father...

251
00:20:34.359 --> 00:20:37.696
my nephew. Lord Lyonel. perished by fire...

252
00:20:38.321 --> 00:20:39.448
And his son too.

253
00:20:39.990 --> 00:20:41.992
...here in this damp place?

254
00:20:44.411 --> 00:20:47.664
It was the first fire here since Balerion
ended the line of Harren the Black.

255
00:20:48.457 --> 00:20:50.625
Even in summer.
we struggle to light the hearths.

256
00:20:50.709 --> 00:20:54.045
So. no. you will find no loyalty
to Larys Strong here. my prince.

257
00:20:54.129 --> 00:20:55.172
"Your Grace."

258
00:21:00.677 --> 00:21:02.471
Forgive me. I... I. um...

259
00:21:04.389 --> 00:21:07.350
I... I'd only assumed that. as consort...

260
00:21:07.434 --> 00:21:09.853
Then we are reminded
of the perilousness of assumption.

261
00:21:11.480 --> 00:21:12.481
Indeed.

262
00:21:15.609 --> 00:21:16.735
Your Grace.

263
00:21:22.073 --> 00:21:25.410
What. then. brings you
to our corner of the Riverlands?

264
00:21:25.494 --> 00:21:27.996
Harrenhal is the largest castle
in the Seven Kingdoms.

265
00:21:29.581 --> 00:21:31.625
Or perhaps that has escaped
your attention.

266
00:21:31.708 --> 00:21:35.545
It is also. not to be argumentative.
in something of a state of disrepair

267
00:21:35.629 --> 00:21:38.882
since your forebear incinerated
much of it with his dragon.

268
00:21:38.965 --> 00:21:42.260
That is precisely why we must bring it
into a state of repair.

269
00:21:43.261 --> 00:21:45.680
Even if we possessed the coin. my pr...

270
00:21:47.891 --> 00:21:50.060
Your Grace. To what possible end?

271
00:21:50.143 --> 00:21:54.105
There are 40.000 swords in the Riverlands.
the largest undeclared host in the realm.

272
00:21:54.189 --> 00:21:56.858
Only Harrenhal is of a size enough
to garrison them.

273
00:21:56.942 --> 00:22:00.237
You should know that a substantial number
of those swords have now declared

274
00:22:00.320 --> 00:22:01.738
and are presently at war.

275
00:22:01.821 --> 00:22:05.242
Houses Bracken and Blackwood
have long detested one another.

276
00:22:05.325 --> 00:22:07.160
- Why?
- Oh. well...

277
00:22:09.287 --> 00:22:10.789
the answer to that is...

278
00:22:11.873 --> 00:22:13.208
lost in time.

279
00:22:14.709 --> 00:22:17.796
Sin begets sin begets sin.

280
00:22:21.174 --> 00:22:24.052
Summon your lord paramount
so that I may treat with him myself

281
00:22:24.135 --> 00:22:25.720
and turn them to our cause.

282
00:22:25.804 --> 00:22:29.057
That would be Lord Grover Tully.
but he grows frail.

283
00:22:29.140 --> 00:22:31.101
It's said he can no longer speak.

284
00:22:32.769 --> 00:22:34.229
Nor seal his bowels.

285
00:22:35.188 --> 00:22:38.608
Begging your pardon for the impression.
His grip on his bannermen is weak.

286
00:22:38.692 --> 00:22:41.712
- They feel they can to do as they please.
- I will speak with him nonetheless.

287
00:22:41.736 --> 00:22:43.572
People should obey their liege lord.

288
00:22:44.781 --> 00:22:46.199
whatever his condition.

289
00:22:47.576 --> 00:22:49.578
Perhaps the presence of the crown...

290
00:22:50.787 --> 00:22:51.913
and a dragon...

291
00:22:52.998 --> 00:22:55.584
will sharpen minds around these parts.

292
00:22:56.960 --> 00:22:58.837
Might I ask. Your Grace.

293
00:23:00.171 --> 00:23:01.590
if you are successful...

294
00:23:01.673 --> 00:23:04.551
Well. when you are successful. what then?

295
00:23:06.344 --> 00:23:08.805
We march on King's Landing
and take the throne.

296
00:23:11.182 --> 00:23:12.642
The throne?

297
00:23:15.770 --> 00:23:19.482
It's a big chair made of swords.

298
00:23:21.318 --> 00:23:23.820
[captain] Standard bearers to the front!

299
00:23:24.446 --> 00:23:26.698
Packhorses to the rear!

300
00:23:27.532 --> 00:23:30.368
Clear a way for the mounted knights!

301
00:23:30.452 --> 00:23:32.454
[dramatic music playing]

302
00:23:41.254 --> 00:23:44.591
Lord Commander.
Your host is mustered and ready to march.

303
00:23:45.091 --> 00:23:46.551
[Gwayne] He enjoys battle.

304
00:23:47.385 --> 00:23:49.012
[Alicent speaking indistinctly]

305
00:23:51.890 --> 00:23:53.850
I'm glad we're together. even briefly.

306
00:23:53.933 --> 00:23:55.226
Ser Criston?

307
00:23:56.645 --> 00:23:59.522
May I present my brother.
Ser Gwayne Hightower.

308
00:23:59.606 --> 00:24:01.608
Arrived last night from Oldtown.

309
00:24:01.691 --> 00:24:02.692
Ser Criston.

310
00:24:03.902 --> 00:24:07.530
Or mayhaps I should say. my Lord Hand?

311
00:24:08.198 --> 00:24:10.075
Ser Gwayne. Welcome to King's Landing.

312
00:24:10.700 --> 00:24:15.705
How exhilarating to arrive at court
after three long months on the road

313
00:24:15.789 --> 00:24:19.668
to find my lord father.
who served three kings faithfully.

314
00:24:20.335 --> 00:24:21.836
unseated as Hand to the King.

315
00:24:24.172 --> 00:24:26.966
And by a man from such modest beginnings.

316
00:24:27.592 --> 00:24:28.592
Hm.

317
00:24:29.094 --> 00:24:32.180
What a giddying ascent
the gods have bestowed on you.

318
00:24:33.807 --> 00:24:36.351
Ser Gwayne has volunteered
to accompany you into battle.

319
00:24:40.689 --> 00:24:43.817
- We have a full complement. Your Grace.
- Then you shall have a fuller one.

320
00:24:46.528 --> 00:24:48.196
The march will be hard. ser.

321
00:24:48.947 --> 00:24:52.742
No one is more delighted than I
to march out to war with a Dornishman.

322
00:24:54.411 --> 00:24:55.412
Sister.

323
00:25:03.545 --> 00:25:06.005
May the Seven guide you. good knight.

324
00:25:06.965 --> 00:25:08.842
and lead you not into shadow and death.

325
00:25:11.344 --> 00:25:13.054
I thank Your Grace for her prayers.

326
00:25:16.891 --> 00:25:18.810
And request that she grant her favor.

327
00:25:20.645 --> 00:25:23.314
That her Lord Commander may go
into battle with her blessings...

328
00:25:24.816 --> 00:25:25.817
in his heart.

329
00:25:38.413 --> 00:25:39.414
Your Grace.

330
00:25:47.172 --> 00:25:49.215
[dramatic music building]

331
00:25:51.301 --> 00:25:52.761
- Hyah!
- [horse whinnies]

332
00:26:27.587 --> 00:26:29.297
[indistinct chatter]

333
00:26:29.923 --> 00:26:31.132
[Rhaenys] Still no sightings.

334
00:26:32.717 --> 00:26:37.138
No men. no horses. no ships.

335
00:26:39.474 --> 00:26:41.476
- No dragons.
- Good.

336
00:26:41.559 --> 00:26:45.605
Then we must seize the hour
and act before our enemy does.

337
00:26:46.105 --> 00:26:48.876
They have penetrated our castle walls
and now the Riverlands are aflame

338
00:26:48.900 --> 00:26:50.610
after the Battle of the Burning Mill.

339
00:26:51.694 --> 00:26:53.655
How fares Prince Daemon with our army?

340
00:26:55.490 --> 00:26:58.535
There has been no word
from Prince Daemon. Your Grace.

341
00:26:58.618 --> 00:27:01.329
Then we must press
what advantage we do have.

342
00:27:01.412 --> 00:27:02.747
And what is that?

343
00:27:02.831 --> 00:27:04.707
Dragons. Send them all out.

344
00:27:04.791 --> 00:27:08.628
Start turning Green strongholds
to our cause.

345
00:27:08.711 --> 00:27:10.839
- And burn those who resist.
- [Rhaenyra] No.

346
00:27:11.840 --> 00:27:15.385
If dragons begin fighting dragons.
we invite our own destruction.

347
00:27:16.469 --> 00:27:20.890
Fear of it is in itself a weapon.
The Greens will make the same calculation.

348
00:27:20.974 --> 00:27:23.059
[laughing]

349
00:27:24.060 --> 00:27:27.522
The value of a sword is not
within its scabbard.

350
00:27:28.356 --> 00:27:32.360
[Rhaenyra] We will secure victory
with armies. not with dragons alone.

351
00:27:34.237 --> 00:27:35.655
The Greens understand that.

352
00:27:36.197 --> 00:27:38.408
The Vale and the North will send men.

353
00:27:39.784 --> 00:27:41.160
We must give Daemon time.

354
00:27:42.620 --> 00:27:47.417
Uh. Your Grace. you have witnessed
firsthand just how vulnerable you are.

355
00:27:48.042 --> 00:27:50.003
Prince Daemon is abroad.

356
00:27:50.086 --> 00:27:53.131
and Aegon's factions are enraged
at the death of his son.

357
00:27:53.214 --> 00:27:55.300
You have never been so exposed!

358
00:27:55.383 --> 00:27:59.512
Perhaps it is time for you to think about
secreting yourself somewhere safe.

359
00:27:59.596 --> 00:28:04.726
while we remain here
as a source of distraction for the enemy.

360
00:28:05.393 --> 00:28:07.353
You propose to conduct the war
in my absence?

361
00:28:07.437 --> 00:28:10.148
- It would merely be a precaution.
- It would be treason.

362
00:28:13.943 --> 00:28:16.237
You are fortunate you took it no further.

363
00:28:24.120 --> 00:28:25.872
This council would do well to remember

364
00:28:25.955 --> 00:28:28.458
that their queen wears the crown
of my grandsire.

365
00:28:28.958 --> 00:28:30.543
Jaehaerys the Conciliator.

366
00:28:31.377 --> 00:28:32.754
A prudent ruler.

367
00:28:32.837 --> 00:28:36.633
The wisest of Targaryen kings.
whose reign outlasted every other.

368
00:28:39.177 --> 00:28:40.803
Even Aegon the Conqueror's.

369
00:28:47.352 --> 00:28:51.230
[Corlys] <i>So how do they fare?
The ditherers of Dragonstone.</i>

370
00:28:51.314 --> 00:28:54.692
[Rhaenys] Rhaenyra's council is wayward.
She has a hard task.

371
00:28:55.318 --> 00:28:57.570
I must hope she will rise to it.

372
00:28:57.654 --> 00:29:00.823
But I fear she'll need you by her side
sooner than late.

373
00:29:00.907 --> 00:29:02.267
[Corlys] This bread is still warm.

374
00:29:03.868 --> 00:29:05.620
There's broth too. I made sure of it.

375
00:29:07.330 --> 00:29:08.915
I am no longer an invalid.

376
00:29:16.214 --> 00:29:18.466
I bade farewell to Rhaena
before I returned.

377
00:29:22.637 --> 00:29:23.638
I wish her well.

378
00:29:26.140 --> 00:29:27.517
I would fight a hundred battles

379
00:29:27.600 --> 00:29:30.645
before I went into exile
with none but prattling babes.

380
00:29:32.021 --> 00:29:34.440
One of those babes is your heir.

381
00:29:34.524 --> 00:29:36.192
[scoffs] Joffrey.

382
00:29:36.943 --> 00:29:40.405
A boy of 6 who knows nothing of the sea.

383
00:29:40.488 --> 00:29:41.698
And yet. somehow...

384
00:29:42.573 --> 00:29:45.618
It would displease
neither Rhaenyra nor the gods

385
00:29:45.702 --> 00:29:49.372
if Rhaena were named heir to Driftmark.

386
00:29:51.708 --> 00:29:52.709
Rhaena.

387
00:29:53.292 --> 00:29:54.585
Lord of the Tides?

388
00:29:55.378 --> 00:29:58.131
The girl knows nothing of ships.
nor even of dragons.

389
00:29:58.214 --> 00:30:00.425
There is Rhaena. or there is Joffrey.

390
00:30:01.342 --> 00:30:04.929
Both soon to be far from the creak
of ships and the ocean's roar.

391
00:30:06.848 --> 00:30:10.184
Then. we must hope to...

392
00:30:11.561 --> 00:30:15.523
- see our way forward in time.
- And if there is no time?

393
00:30:18.568 --> 00:30:20.278
We are at war. Corlys.

394
00:30:22.697 --> 00:30:24.449
If something were to befall you...

395
00:30:24.532 --> 00:30:29.412
Then it is well that I am a good sailor.

396
00:30:39.672 --> 00:30:40.840
[sighs]

397
00:30:43.301 --> 00:30:44.635
I have much to attend to.

398
00:30:45.178 --> 00:30:46.387
Corlys...

399
00:30:49.223 --> 00:30:51.225
[poignant music playing]

400
00:30:57.315 --> 00:30:59.317
[dragon chittering]

401
00:31:05.156 --> 00:31:06.824
[dragonkeeper speaking High Valyrian]

402
00:31:10.244 --> 00:31:13.831
[Rhaenyra] I cannot spare
a fighting dragon. but I send what I can.

403
00:31:13.915 --> 00:31:16.751
Stormcloud and Tyraxes are small.
but they will grow.

404
00:31:18.961 --> 00:31:21.839
It is for you to remind Lady Jeyne
of her pledge

405
00:31:21.923 --> 00:31:25.051
and persuade her
of the urgency of our need.

406
00:31:31.974 --> 00:31:34.018
Go safely. sister.

407
00:31:35.645 --> 00:31:37.063
I will be safe enough.

408
00:31:38.106 --> 00:31:41.609
Far away from any danger.
with only babes to nursemaid.

409
00:31:41.692 --> 00:31:46.322
You do a great service. And may yet find
yourself glad to be out of harm's way.

410
00:31:46.405 --> 00:31:49.200
Do not coddle me. Baela.
Grant me at least that dignity.

411
00:31:49.283 --> 00:31:52.078
I meant no insult. We each do what we can.

412
00:31:53.037 --> 00:31:55.748
And here. I think. is some consolation.

413
00:31:58.501 --> 00:32:01.420
Tyraxes and Stormcloud are young
and vulnerable.

414
00:32:02.547 --> 00:32:05.091
These eggs are even more fragile.

415
00:32:06.884 --> 00:32:09.345
But should all come to ruin here...

416
00:32:11.389 --> 00:32:13.182
you will bear our hope for the future.

417
00:32:15.810 --> 00:32:16.811
Your Grace.

418
00:32:17.687 --> 00:32:18.729
[Joffrey] Mommy.

419
00:32:21.816 --> 00:32:23.860
[melancholy music playing]

420
00:33:50.738 --> 00:33:52.740
[handmaid] Yes. [chuckles]

421
00:33:55.034 --> 00:33:56.035
My queen.

422
00:33:58.871 --> 00:34:00.831
I feel sad about Jaehaerys.

423
00:34:02.208 --> 00:34:04.502
But I ought not to. I think.

424
00:34:05.711 --> 00:34:09.465
People die all the time. especially babes.

425
00:34:10.591 --> 00:34:14.428
They're so little.
so they're taken so easily.

426
00:34:17.974 --> 00:34:20.309
Sadness is a condition of motherhood.

427
00:34:20.893 --> 00:34:22.520
There's naught to be gained from it.

428
00:34:27.942 --> 00:34:31.320
That horrid procession
where the smallfolk all stared at me.

429
00:34:31.404 --> 00:34:34.949
I warrant they thought
I had no more right to grief than they do.

430
00:34:36.450 --> 00:34:37.450
[sighs]

431
00:34:37.910 --> 00:34:40.955
Surely. they lose their babes
more than highborn ladies.

432
00:34:45.584 --> 00:34:47.169
The Stranger comes for us all...

433
00:34:48.754 --> 00:34:49.964
queen and commoner.

434
00:34:52.341 --> 00:34:54.385
You have as much claim to grief as anyone.

435
00:34:57.096 --> 00:34:58.097
And you?

436
00:35:03.019 --> 00:35:06.814
I loved Jaehaerys. but my concern has been
more for you and what you have endured.

437
00:35:10.026 --> 00:35:12.445
- Helaena. I...
- I forgive you.

438
00:35:14.322 --> 00:35:15.323
What?

439
00:35:20.578 --> 00:35:22.079
I said that I forgive you.

440
00:35:24.999 --> 00:35:27.209
[breathes deeply]

441
00:35:28.419 --> 00:35:29.962
[Leon] It suits you. Your Grace.

442
00:35:31.213 --> 00:35:32.923
[Martyn] Valyrian steel.

443
00:35:33.007 --> 00:35:34.383
Worth more than a castle.

444
00:35:34.467 --> 00:35:39.347
A sight to stir the passions.
Aegon the Conqueror reborn!

445
00:35:39.430 --> 00:35:40.765
Just get on with it.

446
00:35:40.848 --> 00:35:42.224
[squire] At once. Your Grace.

447
00:35:42.308 --> 00:35:43.976
[Ned] What is your business?

448
00:35:44.060 --> 00:35:46.812
There are rumors that
the king readies himself to fly to war.

449
00:35:47.813 --> 00:35:49.440
[Ned] And what is it to you?

450
00:35:50.149 --> 00:35:51.901
Only that I think
it would benefit all of us

451
00:35:51.984 --> 00:35:55.112
to prevent our king
from being brutally slain by our enemies.

452
00:35:55.196 --> 00:35:58.574
and his body parts scattered to beasts.
and his court come to ruin.

453
00:35:58.657 --> 00:35:59.867
Would you not agree?

454
00:36:03.162 --> 00:36:04.455
What exquisite armor.

455
00:36:07.917 --> 00:36:11.003
I was given the Conqueror's name
and his crown.

456
00:36:11.087 --> 00:36:13.255
so I shall wear his armor to war.

457
00:36:13.339 --> 00:36:14.965
I fly to meet Ser Criston.

458
00:36:16.759 --> 00:36:19.095
A small imposition
before you depart. then. Your Grace.

459
00:36:30.689 --> 00:36:33.651
There are diverse rumors
whispered in the streets of your city.

460
00:36:34.318 --> 00:36:37.571
One such is that Your Grace sends
his forces to battle.

461
00:36:37.655 --> 00:36:40.199
and in his courage and wisdom.
flies with them.

462
00:36:43.119 --> 00:36:46.705
Another is that His Grace
was outwitted by his counselors

463
00:36:46.789 --> 00:36:49.667
and persuaded to fly to war
with Ser Criston.

464
00:36:49.750 --> 00:36:53.629
so that Queen Alicent may reign
in his absence...

465
00:36:54.755 --> 00:36:56.590
with Prince Aemond at her side.

466
00:36:58.759 --> 00:36:59.927
Absurd. of course.

467
00:37:03.514 --> 00:37:05.224
Who spreads these lies?

468
00:37:06.058 --> 00:37:07.268
It matters little.

469
00:37:08.227 --> 00:37:10.229
Tales take on a life of their own.

470
00:37:11.313 --> 00:37:12.481
Like weeds.

471
00:37:13.107 --> 00:37:14.483
Unless they are tended.

472
00:37:16.152 --> 00:37:17.445
Well. tend to them. then.

473
00:37:26.454 --> 00:37:27.621
Lord Larys.

474
00:37:29.790 --> 00:37:34.086
My father always said
he had no use for a Master of Whisperers.

475
00:37:35.629 --> 00:37:39.467
And yet. I find myself wanting for one.

476
00:37:41.469 --> 00:37:43.429
I should be glad of your talents.

477
00:37:48.142 --> 00:37:49.810
You honor me. Your Grace.

478
00:37:56.609 --> 00:37:59.069
[Martyn] Shall we escort you
to the Dragonpit. Your Grace?

479
00:38:02.907 --> 00:38:03.949
Uh...

480
00:38:06.577 --> 00:38:08.454
I think. mayhaps.
I shall fly another day.

481
00:38:08.537 --> 00:38:09.453
[Leon] Mm-hm.

482
00:38:09.455 --> 00:38:10.413
- Mm-hm.
- Yeah.

483
00:38:10.414 --> 00:38:12.583
- It does seem wise. on reflection.
- Mm. Mm.

484
00:38:12.666 --> 00:38:14.460
[Ned] You could come out with us. my king.

485
00:38:14.543 --> 00:38:16.795
Ser Martyn has a new squire
that wants bedding in.

486
00:38:17.421 --> 00:38:19.465
He's never fucked a woman.

487
00:38:20.341 --> 00:38:21.800
But you are sworn to chastity now.

488
00:38:21.884 --> 00:38:23.135
[all laughing]

489
00:38:25.179 --> 00:38:26.555
Of course. Your Grace.

490
00:38:26.639 --> 00:38:27.723
[chuckles]

491
00:38:33.145 --> 00:38:34.146
Yes. Your Grace.

492
00:38:37.691 --> 00:38:38.691
Hm.

493
00:38:39.527 --> 00:38:41.529
[percussive music playing]

494
00:38:47.576 --> 00:38:49.453
[festive chatter]

495
00:38:49.787 --> 00:38:51.622
[people shouting excitedly]

496
00:38:56.126 --> 00:38:57.711
Yes. That's the one.

497
00:39:00.172 --> 00:39:02.216
[indistinct chatter]

498
00:39:04.093 --> 00:39:05.135
[man] Hello.

499
00:39:06.762 --> 00:39:08.764
[joyful fiddle music playing]

500
00:39:08.847 --> 00:39:11.767
- Ah. right!
- There he is!

501
00:39:11.850 --> 00:39:13.978
No. no. no. Don't tell me you're going.

502
00:39:14.061 --> 00:39:15.901
- I'm not going yet.
- I've only just got here.

503
00:39:17.523 --> 00:39:20.025
You're not meant to be here.
Don't worry. I won't tell her.

504
00:39:20.109 --> 00:39:21.318
There he is!

505
00:39:21.402 --> 00:39:23.296
How'd you get here so...?
I've got a good one for you.

506
00:39:23.320 --> 00:39:26.657
- Ulf! Ulf! Come on. son! Come on!
- [Ulf] Hey there. lads.

507
00:39:27.700 --> 00:39:31.787
Turns out. it was her sister.
No one's ever told me.

508
00:39:32.830 --> 00:39:37.001
Hello. hello. hello. Take that. You'll get
your pound of flesh. don't worry.

509
00:39:37.084 --> 00:39:38.794
Sit yourself down. mate.

510
00:39:38.877 --> 00:39:40.879
I've been telling this fellow
all about you.

511
00:39:40.963 --> 00:39:44.466
- Oh. lads. I've had quite a day of it.
- Yeah?

512
00:39:44.550 --> 00:39:46.802
I'm not sure I'm much for talking.

513
00:39:47.761 --> 00:39:51.223
Although. you know.
a wet whistle works wonders.

514
00:39:52.057 --> 00:39:53.142
Mm.

515
00:39:54.226 --> 00:39:56.186
[laughing]

516
00:39:56.270 --> 00:39:58.981
Come on. love.
Give us a flagon over there. yeah?

517
00:39:59.064 --> 00:40:02.234
Here you are my darling.
one for the flagon. one for yourself.

518
00:40:02.318 --> 00:40:03.944
There's a good girl. eh?

519
00:40:04.486 --> 00:40:05.821
- [gasps]
- [man laughing]

520
00:40:08.449 --> 00:40:10.200
No sense of fun. some of them.

521
00:40:10.284 --> 00:40:11.827
For you. man of Dorne.

522
00:40:12.786 --> 00:40:13.871
Dornish. are you?

523
00:40:14.747 --> 00:40:15.914
Yes. I am.

524
00:40:15.998 --> 00:40:18.626
The part of Westeros
my house never settled.

525
00:40:18.709 --> 00:40:22.588
Although it's said even Dorne mourned
the passing of my grandsire. Is that so?

526
00:40:23.213 --> 00:40:24.798
Who was your grandsire?

527
00:40:24.882 --> 00:40:26.884
[joyful fiddle music continues playing]

528
00:40:28.469 --> 00:40:30.763
They call him the Conciliator.

529
00:40:31.889 --> 00:40:32.890
King Jaehaerys?

530
00:40:32.973 --> 00:40:34.058
Shh!

531
00:40:35.934 --> 00:40:39.021
A thousand apologies. Please. continue.

532
00:40:39.104 --> 00:40:41.565
Look. I...
I really shouldn't be telling you this.

533
00:40:42.733 --> 00:40:45.903
- Could cost me my head.
- You are saying you're a Targaryen?

534
00:40:45.986 --> 00:40:47.488
[shushing]

535
00:40:51.825 --> 00:40:54.787
I am the son of Baelon the Brave.

536
00:40:55.913 --> 00:41:00.668
Bastard brother to Prince Daemon
and the late King Viserys.

537
00:41:00.751 --> 00:41:05.422
Uncle to the one true queen.
Rhaenyra Targaryen.

538
00:41:06.965 --> 00:41:09.760
The blood of the dragon
runs through these veins.

539
00:41:09.843 --> 00:41:13.180
And. yes. men would take my head for it.

540
00:41:15.891 --> 00:41:18.102
A Dragonseed must watch his own neck

541
00:41:18.185 --> 00:41:21.438
when he has no white-cloaked guardsmen
to do it for him.

542
00:41:23.732 --> 00:41:26.151
You do not look very much
like King Viserys.

543
00:41:26.944 --> 00:41:28.362
Or Prince Daemon.

544
00:41:31.490 --> 00:41:34.618
- How do you know what they look like?
- He speaks truth. right enough.

545
00:41:34.702 --> 00:41:36.203
Look. you can tell.

546
00:41:37.454 --> 00:41:38.370
By his hair.

547
00:41:38.372 --> 00:41:39.288
- [all laughing]
- Yeah.

548
00:41:39.289 --> 00:41:41.667
'Cause I'm their half-brother.
you fuckwits.

549
00:41:41.750 --> 00:41:44.128
I'll tell you who else
doesn't have silver hair.

550
00:41:44.211 --> 00:41:48.716
The rightful heir to the Iron Throne.
my nephew. Prince Jacaerys Velaryon.

551
00:41:48.799 --> 00:41:50.259
[music and chatter stop]

552
00:41:52.720 --> 00:41:54.221
Here's your other nephew.

553
00:42:01.687 --> 00:42:04.982
- All hail the king!
- [all] All hail the king!

554
00:42:06.608 --> 00:42:10.446
Drinks for all.
At the pleasure of the Crown!

555
00:42:10.529 --> 00:42:12.072
[patrons cheering]

556
00:42:14.783 --> 00:42:16.952
Whoo! At the pleasure of the Crown.

557
00:42:18.537 --> 00:42:20.622
Sit down. Sit yourself down.

558
00:42:20.706 --> 00:42:22.708
- Sit!
- [Aegon] Drink the wine. boy.

559
00:42:22.791 --> 00:42:24.877
- Come on. lad!
- [Aegon] Drink up. little piggy.

560
00:42:25.836 --> 00:42:29.590
- Young squire!
- This night is for you. You!

561
00:42:29.673 --> 00:42:31.341
[indistinct chatter]

562
00:42:31.425 --> 00:42:33.218
[Martyn] More! Come on. More!

563
00:42:38.056 --> 00:42:40.809
Did I...?
Did I tell you I came here as a lad?

564
00:42:41.477 --> 00:42:46.940
It's. mm. a little tame but as good
a place as any to get it wet.

565
00:42:47.024 --> 00:42:48.275
[laughs]

566
00:42:48.358 --> 00:42:50.444
I know just the tutor for you. my boy.

567
00:42:51.987 --> 00:42:54.072
[man and woman moaning]

568
00:42:54.156 --> 00:42:55.199
No.

569
00:42:55.282 --> 00:42:57.201
She's worth three times the price.

570
00:42:57.284 --> 00:42:59.119
[moaning]

571
00:42:59.870 --> 00:43:03.207
Oh. Gods be good. [laughs]

572
00:43:03.290 --> 00:43:04.958
- That's you!
- Her name is. uh...

573
00:43:05.501 --> 00:43:09.838
Silvi or Selyse or something like that.

574
00:43:09.922 --> 00:43:11.089
[coughs]

575
00:43:12.758 --> 00:43:14.718
[laughing]

576
00:43:18.764 --> 00:43:20.599
Aemond the Fierce!

577
00:43:20.682 --> 00:43:21.682
[laughs]

578
00:43:21.725 --> 00:43:23.977
You have come so far

579
00:43:24.061 --> 00:43:26.897
and yet you still lie
with your very first.

580
00:43:26.980 --> 00:43:28.315
[sniffles. then chuckles]

581
00:43:28.398 --> 00:43:31.109
What a fine. sweet thing.

582
00:43:31.193 --> 00:43:33.111
[laughing]

583
00:43:33.195 --> 00:43:34.988
Did you fuck her like a hound?

584
00:43:35.072 --> 00:43:36.448
[barking]

585
00:43:36.532 --> 00:43:38.575
[laughing]

586
00:43:39.326 --> 00:43:41.411
You see. I did not exaggerate.

587
00:43:41.495 --> 00:43:44.540
Such is the madam's prowess.
that even now.

588
00:43:44.623 --> 00:43:47.209
my brother will not sample another.

589
00:43:49.962 --> 00:43:51.755
Hard luck for your squire. though.

590
00:43:51.839 --> 00:43:55.592
As you can see. she...
She's now very much occupied.

591
00:43:55.676 --> 00:43:57.678
[laughing]

592
00:44:04.810 --> 00:44:06.645
Your squire is welcome to her.

593
00:44:08.397 --> 00:44:10.315
One whore is as good as another.

594
00:44:12.484 --> 00:44:14.486
[Aegon continues laughing]

595
00:44:18.323 --> 00:44:19.783
[Aegon] Ah...

596
00:44:37.175 --> 00:44:39.177
[poignant music playing]

597
00:45:27.601 --> 00:45:28.602
[Cole] Ser Gwayne!

598
00:45:29.227 --> 00:45:30.228
Halt!

599
00:45:36.026 --> 00:45:38.612
Ser Gwayne.
our company is camped back yonder.

600
00:45:38.695 --> 00:45:41.156
Mm. On the cold. hard ground.

601
00:45:41.990 --> 00:45:43.575
Which is why we make for the Bull.

602
00:45:44.284 --> 00:45:46.828
A tavern with an excellent reputation.
on the Rosby Road.

603
00:45:46.912 --> 00:45:48.622
Not two miles away. if memory serves.

604
00:45:48.705 --> 00:45:51.083
We march to make the first strike
in the name of His Grace.

605
00:45:51.917 --> 00:45:55.128
I assure you. my nephew will not
begrudge me a night of comfort.

606
00:46:01.677 --> 00:46:03.220
If it soothes your brow. Cole.

607
00:46:04.096 --> 00:46:06.390
we will rendezvous
with your army at first light.

608
00:46:07.265 --> 00:46:10.060
Or if their wine is good.
perhaps a little after first light.

609
00:46:13.146 --> 00:46:14.523
- We're exposed.
- What?

610
00:46:17.150 --> 00:46:19.361
- [Gwayne] Cole?
- [Cole] Get to the trees!

611
00:46:19.444 --> 00:46:20.737
[knight] Hyah!

612
00:46:20.821 --> 00:46:23.115
[Gwayne] Hyah! Hyah!

613
00:46:26.118 --> 00:46:27.911
[dramatic music playing]

614
00:46:34.960 --> 00:46:36.878
[dragon growling]

615
00:46:36.962 --> 00:46:37.963
[screeches]

616
00:46:40.674 --> 00:46:42.843
[growling]

617
00:46:45.053 --> 00:46:46.972
[roaring]

618
00:46:51.435 --> 00:46:53.478
Hyah! Hyah!

619
00:46:54.604 --> 00:46:56.481
[Gwayne] Hyah! Come on!

620
00:46:59.484 --> 00:47:01.194
[roars]

621
00:47:04.072 --> 00:47:05.657
- Hyah!
- Hyah! Hyah!

622
00:47:08.368 --> 00:47:09.453
[screeches]

623
00:47:10.871 --> 00:47:12.289
[growling]

624
00:47:12.372 --> 00:47:13.498
Hyah!

625
00:47:14.332 --> 00:47:15.417
[speaking High Valyrian]

626
00:47:16.251 --> 00:47:17.294
[screeches]

627
00:47:22.382 --> 00:47:24.593
[growls. then screeches]

628
00:47:28.388 --> 00:47:29.765
- [horse neighs]
- [all panting]

629
00:47:29.848 --> 00:47:32.059
[breathing heavily]

630
00:47:33.435 --> 00:47:35.437
[ominous music playing]

631
00:47:39.107 --> 00:47:40.233
[dragon screeches]

632
00:48:02.714 --> 00:48:03.757
[shouts in High Valyrian]

633
00:48:04.549 --> 00:48:06.551
[screeches]

634
00:48:11.681 --> 00:48:13.308
[panting]

635
00:48:18.355 --> 00:48:19.815
A good showing. Ser Criston.

636
00:48:23.735 --> 00:48:25.028
I am in your debt.

637
00:48:25.112 --> 00:48:26.947
They know we're abroad.
They'll be hunting.

638
00:48:27.614 --> 00:48:30.700
We must move under the trees
and by cover of dark. starting tonight.

639
00:48:32.035 --> 00:48:33.703
And no fucking inns.

640
00:48:37.374 --> 00:48:38.583
[Baela] <i>Ser Criston Cole.</i>

641
00:48:40.043 --> 00:48:42.796
With some half dozen other knights.
I'm sure of it.

642
00:48:42.879 --> 00:48:45.048
Perhaps a scout party for a greater army.

643
00:48:45.132 --> 00:48:47.092
[Gerardys] The ravens confirm it.
Your Grace.

644
00:48:47.175 --> 00:48:51.221
Lord Farring has reported
a larger force moving northeast.

645
00:48:51.304 --> 00:48:52.889
towards Rosby.

646
00:48:53.473 --> 00:48:56.143
Could you be certain it was Cole
from such a great height?

647
00:48:56.226 --> 00:48:58.186
It was not such a great height.
Your Grace.

648
00:49:01.022 --> 00:49:04.484
You said not to engage.
so I didn't. Exactly.

649
00:49:04.568 --> 00:49:05.652
[Bartimos] Your Grace.

650
00:49:05.735 --> 00:49:08.697
We commend the Lady Baela
for her sharp eyes.

651
00:49:08.780 --> 00:49:12.200
But we can tarry no longer.
The time for action is surely now.

652
00:49:12.284 --> 00:49:13.910
Your Grace. I must agree.

653
00:49:13.994 --> 00:49:17.789
And request your permission to return
to Rook's Rest and fortify my lands.

654
00:49:17.873 --> 00:49:21.251
I shouldn't fret. Lord Simon.
They'll be making for Harrenhal.

655
00:49:21.334 --> 00:49:23.170
'Tis Prince Daemon who ought to worry.

656
00:49:23.253 --> 00:49:24.880
Prince Daemon has Caraxes.

657
00:49:24.963 --> 00:49:29.092
Cole will look to increase his numbers.
and he may call upon a dragon of his own.

658
00:49:29.176 --> 00:49:32.179
This is why you must act now. Your Grace.

659
00:49:32.804 --> 00:49:35.473
Loose the dragons.
Root Cole out and burn him.

660
00:49:38.518 --> 00:49:40.061
[suspenseful music playing]

661
00:49:51.448 --> 00:49:53.116
I have heard your arguments.

662
00:49:55.076 --> 00:49:56.244
And will consider them.

663
00:50:00.707 --> 00:50:02.709
[murmuring]

664
00:50:37.369 --> 00:50:39.371
[footsteps approaching]

665
00:50:55.011 --> 00:50:56.763
[door rattling]

666
00:51:19.536 --> 00:51:21.538
[woman humming]

667
00:51:31.381 --> 00:51:33.591
[humming continues]

668
00:51:42.809 --> 00:51:45.103
[humming continues]

669
00:51:56.031 --> 00:51:58.491
Always coming and going. aren't you?

670
00:52:05.081 --> 00:52:07.208
And I have to clean up afterwards.

671
00:52:12.422 --> 00:52:14.257
[resumes humming]

672
00:52:35.195 --> 00:52:37.197
[unsettling music playing]

673
00:52:44.037 --> 00:52:46.039
[birds chirping]

674
00:52:48.833 --> 00:52:50.460
You will die in this place.

675
00:53:08.144 --> 00:53:09.646
[Elinda]...never in the castle.

676
00:53:10.188 --> 00:53:13.066
My youngest brother. Emmon.
would stand guard

677
00:53:13.149 --> 00:53:14.984
with the soldiers when he was 3 years old.

678
00:53:15.068 --> 00:53:17.112
Father sent him to the Citadel.
If you ask me...

679
00:53:17.195 --> 00:53:18.321
Thank you. Elinda.

680
00:53:19.572 --> 00:53:20.698
Your Grace.

681
00:53:28.164 --> 00:53:30.458
What do you know of the movements
of Alicent Hightower?

682
00:53:35.463 --> 00:53:37.090
Would you take her hostage?

683
00:53:38.007 --> 00:53:40.093
Or kill her outright?

684
00:53:40.176 --> 00:53:43.221
I would speak with her. Myself.

685
00:53:43.972 --> 00:53:45.682
Killing her would be easier.

686
00:53:47.809 --> 00:53:50.645
If war can be averted.
it is my duty to avert it.

687
00:53:51.688 --> 00:53:53.940
I've reason to believe
she may be of the same opinion.

688
00:53:55.191 --> 00:53:58.361
She sent a raven.
She has expressed her remorse.

689
00:53:58.445 --> 00:54:01.030
I can have a message brought to her.
In secret.

690
00:54:01.114 --> 00:54:05.618
She would not agree to it.
She would suspect some subterfuge.

691
00:54:06.327 --> 00:54:08.079
As would I if I received such a message.

692
00:54:08.830 --> 00:54:12.000
I must see her face-to-face.

693
00:54:15.503 --> 00:54:17.255
She is the queen dowager.

694
00:54:17.338 --> 00:54:20.383
She goes nowhere
without many eyes watching her.

695
00:54:24.387 --> 00:54:25.388
Unless...

696
00:54:29.476 --> 00:54:31.478
- It is fraught.
- Speak it.

697
00:54:32.937 --> 00:54:36.274
There are fishing boats aplenty
in the bay.

698
00:54:37.358 --> 00:54:41.070
The city depends on them.
Daemon made the journey unhindered.

699
00:54:41.613 --> 00:54:44.741
- But if I'm recognized...
- You may be surprised to learn it.

700
00:54:44.824 --> 00:54:49.245
but most folk pay no mind to a woman
who has not dressed as a queen

701
00:54:49.329 --> 00:54:51.664
or allured herself for the eyes of men.

702
00:54:55.043 --> 00:55:00.006
So I make my way to the Red Keep.
I presume. and ring the bell?

703
00:55:00.757 --> 00:55:03.343
Or do I scale the wall
and enter at her window?

704
00:55:03.426 --> 00:55:05.595
There is one place Alicent goes.

705
00:55:06.346 --> 00:55:08.306
outside the castle walls...

706
00:55:10.016 --> 00:55:12.143
where you may yet find her alone.

707
00:55:15.605 --> 00:55:17.607
[suspenseful music playing]

708
00:55:30.411 --> 00:55:31.454
[guard 1] Wait there!

709
00:55:32.038 --> 00:55:33.164
Open those sacks!

710
00:55:33.248 --> 00:55:35.041
[guard 2] Stop! Search the carts.

711
00:55:35.124 --> 00:55:36.477
[guard 1] We're searching
all of your bags.

712
00:55:36.501 --> 00:55:39.061
- [guard 2] Give me your sword.
- [guard 3] Move it. Quick there!

713
00:55:40.046 --> 00:55:41.756
[guard 4] What's your business here?

714
00:55:41.839 --> 00:55:44.676
[guard 3] Move them on through.
Move them on through!

715
00:55:45.802 --> 00:55:47.804
[indistinct chatter]

716
00:55:51.432 --> 00:55:53.434
[suspenseful music playing]

717
00:56:20.753 --> 00:56:22.422
[bell tolling]

718
00:56:32.348 --> 00:56:34.309
[suspenseful music continues]

719
00:56:56.956 --> 00:56:58.958
[bell tolling]

720
00:57:16.851 --> 00:57:18.853
[voices chanting]

721
00:58:05.566 --> 00:58:06.818
[sighs]

722
00:58:07.694 --> 00:58:09.237
- [gasps]
- No. No. Shh.

723
00:58:09.320 --> 00:58:10.530
Wha...?

724
00:58:10.613 --> 00:58:11.739
Shh.

725
00:58:12.699 --> 00:58:14.826
- Wha...?
- I must speak with you.

726
00:58:19.747 --> 00:58:21.249
If I cry out?

727
00:58:22.166 --> 00:58:24.711
Your knights would find me.
I would be taken or slain.

728
00:58:25.503 --> 00:58:27.130
Though not before I killed you.

729
00:58:28.965 --> 00:58:29.966
And then what?

730
00:58:34.137 --> 00:58:35.513
I have begun badly.

731
00:58:35.596 --> 00:58:36.597
[scoffs]

732
00:58:49.360 --> 00:58:54.282
We watched the tourney together.
you and I. the day my brother was born.

733
00:58:56.534 --> 00:58:58.035
We knew. even then.

734
00:58:58.119 --> 00:59:00.496
that men trained up for battle
are eager to fight.

735
00:59:01.164 --> 00:59:03.040
To seek blood and glory.

736
00:59:03.750 --> 00:59:04.876
But you. I...

737
00:59:07.503 --> 00:59:10.173
I know you do not have
that desire within you.

738
00:59:16.971 --> 00:59:18.598
Rhaenys has counseled me.

739
00:59:19.515 --> 00:59:23.102
She said she saw in you a wish to avert
the worst of what may now come.

740
00:59:26.814 --> 00:59:28.357
So you've come to surrender. then?

741
00:59:30.443 --> 00:59:34.697
I have come to see if we may uncover
some path towards peace.

742
00:59:36.449 --> 00:59:39.160
My dragons are restless.
They smell battle.

743
00:59:39.243 --> 00:59:43.706
- But if you and I may come to terms...
- There are no terms now.

744
00:59:45.166 --> 00:59:48.753
You have no army. Your allies turn
from you when they hear of your depravity.

745
00:59:48.836 --> 00:59:51.231
Your hands bloodied in a crime
I could never have imagined...

746
00:59:51.255 --> 00:59:52.548
The trespass was not mine.

747
00:59:54.217 --> 00:59:55.510
Oh. think what you will.

748
00:59:56.594 --> 00:59:59.114
I am a mother too. and you have yet
to answer for the murder of my son.

749
00:59:59.138 --> 01:00:01.808
- I repudiate that act with all my heart.
- Of course. you do.

750
01:00:03.142 --> 01:00:05.102
And the usurping
of my rightful inheritance?

751
01:00:23.663 --> 01:00:25.724
Have you now stooped so low
that you will countenance

752
01:00:25.748 --> 01:00:27.917
the suffering and death of thousands.

753
01:00:28.000 --> 01:00:30.878
- in order that your feckless son...
- Your father changed his mind.

754
01:00:31.671 --> 01:00:35.258
Oh. so you say. And so your father
has proclaimed to the realm.

755
01:00:36.133 --> 01:00:38.010
I saw the king that night.

756
01:00:39.262 --> 01:00:42.974
Mere hours before I left him.
he had affirmed my right to the throne.

757
01:00:43.057 --> 01:00:45.768
A right he upheld steadfastly

758
01:00:45.852 --> 01:00:47.854
every day of his life
after my mother died.

759
01:00:50.064 --> 01:00:52.775
And yet you will maintain
that his mind was changed in an instant.

760
01:00:52.859 --> 01:00:54.068
I will.

761
01:00:55.570 --> 01:00:56.612
You lie.

762
01:00:58.072 --> 01:00:59.156
No. Rhaenyra.

763
01:01:02.660 --> 01:01:04.328
My father loved me. Alicent.

764
01:01:05.246 --> 01:01:07.164
And I believe he loved you too.

765
01:01:09.166 --> 01:01:11.127
Did you betray him at the very last?

766
01:01:12.795 --> 01:01:15.756
When was your plan first laid?
Was your ambition so keen...?

767
01:01:15.840 --> 01:01:19.760
He changed his mind. Rhaenyra.
He changed his mind.

768
01:01:24.974 --> 01:01:27.560
I swear this to you
on the memory of my mother.

769
01:01:32.148 --> 01:01:34.400
I have been at times unkind
but never untrue.

770
01:01:35.526 --> 01:01:37.286
I pronounced
before all gathered in that room

771
01:01:37.320 --> 01:01:39.280
that you would make a fine queen.

772
01:01:40.448 --> 01:01:42.450
Do you think me capable
of such naked deceit?

773
01:02:03.304 --> 01:02:05.014
What did he say? At the end?

774
01:02:08.893 --> 01:02:10.519
Did he speak my name?

775
01:02:14.106 --> 01:02:15.274
[sighs]

776
01:02:31.082 --> 01:02:32.249
He was weary.

777
01:02:35.127 --> 01:02:37.004
It was hard. at times. to understand.

778
01:02:39.966 --> 01:02:41.509
But he spoke Aegon's name.

779
01:02:50.059 --> 01:02:52.937
He said he was the prince
that was promised to unite the realm.

780
01:02:54.188 --> 01:02:56.524
- What?
- I desire peace as you do. but if it is...

781
01:02:56.607 --> 01:03:00.319
Did my father use those words?
"The Prince That Was Promised"?

782
01:03:00.403 --> 01:03:02.697
[tense music playing]

783
01:03:02.780 --> 01:03:04.156
Did he?

784
01:03:04.240 --> 01:03:05.282
Yes. he did.

785
01:03:09.078 --> 01:03:12.915
He spoke to you
of the Song of Ice and Fire?

786
01:03:20.089 --> 01:03:22.466
It's a story he once told.

787
01:03:23.926 --> 01:03:25.636
About Aegon the Conqueror.

788
01:03:31.684 --> 01:03:33.060
The Conqueror.

789
01:03:51.454 --> 01:03:54.099
- You must go. before you are discovered.
- There has been a mistake.

790
01:03:54.123 --> 01:03:55.958
- There's been no mistake.
- Please.

791
01:03:58.127 --> 01:03:59.920
You can prevent this. Alicent.

792
01:04:01.672 --> 01:04:03.299
A terrible war is looming.

793
01:04:03.883 --> 01:04:06.552
And even victory may be so bloody
as to be counted a loss.

794
01:04:06.635 --> 01:04:10.431
- Do not let your pride blind you to what...
- There has been no mistake.

795
01:04:14.602 --> 01:04:16.353
My father is gone from court.

796
01:04:18.022 --> 01:04:19.523
Cole is on the march. Aemond...

797
01:04:22.610 --> 01:04:23.861
You know what Aemond is.

798
01:04:31.035 --> 01:04:32.244
It's too late. Rhaenyra.

799
01:04:32.328 --> 01:04:33.329
Alicent...

800
01:04:38.000 --> 01:04:41.003
[female singer vocalizing]

801
01:05:03.901 --> 01:05:06.278
[somber music playing]
